## About

This project recreates a fun and competitive paddle-ball game where players control paddles to hit a moving ball back and forth. It supports both **Player vs Player** and **Player vs Bot (AI) ** modes with multiple difficulty levels.

Built with simplicity and gameplay in mind, the game features smooth paddle movement, a responsive AI bot, and an intuitive scoring and life system.

---

## Features

- Two game modes:  
  - Player vs Bot [AI] (with adjustable difficulty)  
  - Player vs Player  
- Three difficulty levels for the Bot [AI]: Easy, Medium, Hard  
- Real-time paddle and ball physics with collision detection  
- Score and life tracking for each player  
- Reset and replay functionality after game over  
- Simple and clean UI with score and lives display  
- Smooth paddle control and AI paddle movement  

---

## Controls

| Action               | Player 1       | Player 2 / Bot [AI]         |
|----------------------|----------------|-----------------------|
| Move paddle up       | W              | Up Arrow (Player)      |
| Move paddle down     | S              | Down Arrow (Player)    |
| Select menu option   | 1, 2, 3 keys   | N/A                   |
| Restart game         | ENTER          | N/A                   |

---

## Game Modes & Difficulty

- **Player vs Bot:** Play against an AI-controlled paddle. Select difficulty before starting:  
  - Easy: Slower AI paddle speed  
  - Medium: Balanced AI speed  
  - Hard: Fast, challenging AI paddle  
- **Player vs Player:** Two human players control separate paddles.

---

## Installation & Running

### Prerequisites

- C++ compiler supporting C++11 or later  
- [raylib](https://www.raylib.com/) installed on your system

